  "text": "[31] The magnetic field low could be caused by lowmagnetization intrusive rock below the ridge axis. Intrusives may be poorly magnetized relative to extrusives because of their crystalline nature [CITATION_1] Smith and Banerjee, 1986; [CITATION_2] or because they not yet cooled below the Curie or magnetic unblocking temperatures [e.g., [CITATION_3] . While either scenario assumes the effects of intrusions, we distinguish between the two because of implications for the dimensions of the body, shown below.",
